# Memory Index (Sanitized Example)

# This is the always-loaded index file. Content lives in topic files.
# Target: under 40 lines. Pure index, no content.

## Topic Files

| File | Contents |
|------|----------|
| `memory/operating-system.md` | Org structure, workflow patterns |
| `memory/product.md` | Core product details and architecture |
| `memory/partnerships.md` | Key relationships and status |
| `memory/infrastructure.md` | Tech stack, tools, known gaps |
| `memory/anti-patterns.md` | Known failures to avoid |
| `memory/feedback_style.md` | User corrections on communication style |
| `memory/priorities.md` | Current P0/P1/P2 ranked priorities |

## Rules for Memory

- MEMORY.md is always loaded (keep it small)
- Topic files are loaded on demand (can be deep)
- Update or remove memories that become outdated
- No duplicate memories (check before writing)
- Memory types: user, feedback, project, reference
- Never store: code patterns (read the code), git history (use git log), debug solutions (the fix is in the commit)
